A mysterious vampire slaying kit - complete with holy water, a mallet and a set of wooden stakes - is going on show in a new exhibition dedicated to the strange and supernatural world of the gothic.

The ghoulish box, which also includes a crucifix, rosary beads and a pistol, is part of a new exhibition at the British Library in central London which opens tomorrow.

Some believe the kits date back to Victorian times, with others saying they are more modern - and inspired by the famous Hammer Horror films.

