Curator Greg Buzwell said: 'They really do exist and we're very fortunate and lucky to have this. 

'Every component you see in there dates from the Victorian era so you've got the mallet, the stakes, the crucifix and the holy water, etc.

'But there is a mystery around them. There is no real evidence of them existing prior to about 1970.'

Mr Buzwell said he could only speculate as to how many were made and for whom.  

'There are 60 or 70 of them thought to be in existence. We think probably a lot of them were maybe made for eccentric collectors.

